AI MODIFICATIONS TO MY RECIPE
=======================================================

1) Espresso pancake
        1 tsp espresso powder 
        reduce the amount of vanilla extract to 1/2 tsp
        a pinch of cinnamon 
        drizzle ganache on top (chocolate sauce, research how to make)

2) chia pancakes 
        1 tbsp chia seeds in the batter (hydrated in liquid for best texture)
            Mix 1 tbsp chia seeds with 2 tbsp water or buttermilk. Let sit for 10 minutes until gel-like. This prevents crunchiness and adds moisture.
        1/2 tsp cardamom
        1/4 cup chopped pecans  in the batter
        A drizzle of honey or maple syrup in the batter for subtle sweetness 
        Top with fresh berries, a dollop of Greek yogurt, and a drizzle of honey for a wholesome finish.

3) orange zest pancakes 
        1 tsp finely grated orange zest (from a fresh orange)
        1 tbsp fresh orange juice (boosts citrus flavor without thinning too much)
        Pinch of cinnamon (pairs beautifully with orange)
        Put orange segments on top, along with maple syrup - apparently they will pair well 

